  "usageNotes": {
    "teacherGuidance": "Use real class data to create pictographs on the board. Start with a key of 1 picture = 1 item, then progress to 1 picture = 2 items. Let students choose fun symbols.",
    "parentGuidance": "Help your child make a pictograph at home. Draw smiley faces or stars to show how many of each type of fruit you have at home.",
    "studentGuidance": "Pictographs use pictures instead of numbers. Each picture stands for a certain number. Always check the key to know what each picture means!"
